,"1458":"1458","1566":"1566","1489":"1489","1423":"1423","1455":"1455","1389":"1389","1432":"1432","1453":"1453","1496":"1496","about 1454":"about 1454","1418":"1418","1427":"1427","Nottinghamshire, England":"Nottinghamshire, England","Beckering, Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom","Holderness, Yorkshire, England":"Holderness, Yorkshire, England","Benington, Lincolnshire, England":"Benington, Lincolnshire, England","Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Rempston","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["English: locative name from Kempston (Beds)."],"variants":[{"name":"Kempson","meanings":["English (mainly West Midlands): variant of <b>Kempston</b>, a habitational name from Kempston (Bedfordshire), named from an earlier placename <i>Cembes</i> (derived from British <i>cambo-</i> ‘crooked, bent’) + Old English <i>tūn</i> ‘farmstead, estate’."]}]},{"name":"Elizabeth","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["The usual spelling of   Elisabeth   in English. It is recorded in the medieval period, but was made popular by being borne by  Queen Elizabeth I  of England (  1533–1603 ). In the 20th century it again became extremely fashionable, partly because it was the name of  Elizabeth Bowes-Lyon  (  1900–2002 ), who in  1936  became Queen Elizabeth as the wife of King George VI, and after his death in  1952  achieved great public affection as Queen Mother for nearly half a century. Even more influentially, it is the name of her daughter  Queen Elizabeth II  (  b. 1926 )."],"variants":[{"name":"Elisabeth","meanings":["The spelling of   Elizabeth   used in the Authorized Version of the New Testament, and in most modern European languages. This was the name of the mother of John the Baptist (Luke 1:60). Etymologically, the name means ‘God is my oath’, and is therefore identical with <i>Elisheba</i>, the name of the wife of Aaron according to the genealogy at Exodus 6:23. The final element seems to have been altered by association with Hebrew <i>shabbāth</i> ‘Sabbath’."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705197,"age":37,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"Elizabeth Rempston was born in 1418, in Nottinghamshire, England as the daughter of Sir Thomas Rempston and Alice Bekering. She married Sir John Cheney about 1454, in Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter."},"et":{"1418–":"1418–Surnud","1418–Female":"1418–Surnud","1423–1459":"1423–1459","1427–Female":"1427–Surnud","1489–1566":"1489–1566","1423–1489":"1423–1489","1453–1547":"1453–1547","1460–1496":"1460–1496","1389–1458":"1389–1458","–1432":"–1432","1460":"1460","about 1419":"umbes 1419","1547":"1547","1459":"1459","1458":"1458","1566":"1566","1489":"1489","1423":"1423","1455":"1455","1389":"1389","1432":"1432","1453":"1453","1496":"1496","about 1454":"umbes 1454","1418":"1418","1427":"1427","Nottinghamshire, England":"Nottinghamshire, England","Beckering, Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Holderness, Yorkshire, England":"Holderness, Yorkshire, England","Benington, Lincolnshire, England":"Benington, Lincolnshire, England","Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, England"},"fi":{"1418–":"1418–Kuollut","1418–Female":"1418–Kuollut","1423–1459":"1423–1459","1427–Female":"1427–Kuollut","1489–1566":"1489–156